-- BofA taps Moelis banker as financial institutions group vice chairman
-- By Jessica Toonkel
-- Fri Jun 28, 2013 9:29am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/06/28/us-bofa-fig-idUSBRE95R0L920130628

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Bank of America ( BAC.N ) has tapped a Moelis & Company financial services investment banker as vice chairman of its global financial institutions group, according to a memo reviewed by Reuters that was sent to the bank's employees Friday morning. 
 John Binnie, who joined Moelis in 2009, will join Bank of America in the fall, according to the memo from Bill Egan, who heads the global financial institutions group. During his 30-year investment banking career, Binnie has worked at Southgate Alternative Investment Strategies, Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) and Citigroup Inc ( C.N ), according to the memo. (Reporting by Jessica Toonkel; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)